<taxonomicName authorityName="Prathapan &amp; Viraktamath" authorityYear="2009" baseAuthorityName="Medvedev" baseAuthorityYear="2001" box="[273,468,443,464]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Tegyrius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="337" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicolor" status="comb. nov.">Tegyrius bicolor</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[489,622,443,465]" pageId="11" pageNumber="337" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
externally resembles 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Prathapan &amp; Viraktamath" authorityYear="2009" baseAuthorityName="Medvedev" baseAuthorityYear="2001" box="[266,424,474,495]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Tegyrius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="337" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="antennatus" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[266,424,474,495]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="337">T. antennatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[433,553,473,495]" pageId="11" pageNumber="337" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
Both of them are sympatric, and were collected together. The host plant may also be the same. They can be differentiated from each other by the following characters. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Prathapan &amp; Viraktamath" authorityYear="2009" baseAuthorityName="Medvedev" baseAuthorityYear="2001" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Tegyrius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="337" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicolor" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="337">Tegyrius bicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[229,349,596,618]" pageId="11" pageNumber="337" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is a little smaller than 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Prathapan &amp; Viraktamath" authorityYear="2009" baseAuthorityName="Medvedev" baseAuthorityYear="2001" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Tegyrius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="337" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="antennatus" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="337">T. antennatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[185,304,626,648]" pageId="11" pageNumber="337" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
Antennae and legs, except metafemora, are yellow in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Prathapan &amp; Viraktamath" authorityYear="2009" baseAuthorityName="Medvedev" baseAuthorityYear="2001" box="[308,416,657,679]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Tegyrius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="337" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicolor" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[308,416,657,679]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="337">T. bicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[426,548,657,679]" pageId="11" pageNumber="337" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Prathapan &amp; Viraktamath" authorityYear="2009" baseAuthorityName="Medvedev" baseAuthorityYear="2001" box="[599,759,658,679]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Tegyrius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="337" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="antennatus" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[599,759,658,679]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="337">T. antennatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[144,269,687,709]" pageId="11" pageNumber="337" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, antennae and legs are black, with red– brown to piceous portions). Antennomeres are thicker in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Prathapan &amp; Viraktamath" authorityYear="2009" baseAuthorityName="Medvedev" baseAuthorityYear="2001" box="[177,336,749,770]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Tegyrius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="337" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="antennatus" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[177,336,749,770]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="337">T. antennatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[346,468,749,771]" pageId="11" pageNumber="337" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
than in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Prathapan &amp; Viraktamath" authorityYear="2009" baseAuthorityName="Medvedev" baseAuthorityYear="2001" box="[574,683,749,770]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Tegyrius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="337" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicolor" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[574,683,749,770]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="337">T. bicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="11" pageNumber="337" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
The apex of the elytra is strongly convex in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Prathapan &amp; Viraktamath" authorityYear="2009" baseAuthorityName="Medvedev" baseAuthorityYear="2001" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Tegyrius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="337" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicolor" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="337">T. bicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[228,346,810,832]" pageId="11" pageNumber="337" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
compared with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Prathapan &amp; Viraktamath" authorityYear="2009" baseAuthorityName="Medvedev" baseAuthorityYear="2001" box="[529,686,810,831]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Tegyrius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="337" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="antennatus" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[529,686,810,831]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="337">T. antennatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="11" pageNumber="337" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
Subparallel ridges on first abdominal ventrite distally diverge in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Prathapan &amp; Viraktamath" authorityYear="2009" baseAuthorityName="Medvedev" baseAuthorityYear="2001" box="[365,524,872,893]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Tegyrius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="337" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="antennatus" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[365,524,872,893]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="337">T. antennatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[534,655,871,893]" pageId="11" pageNumber="337" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(subparallel ridges distally converge in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Prathapan &amp; Viraktamath" authorityYear="2009" baseAuthorityName="Medvedev" baseAuthorityYear="2001" box="[511,617,902,923]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Tegyrius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="337" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicolor" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[511,617,902,923]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="337">T. bicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[625,748,902,924]" pageId="11" pageNumber="337" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
). The shape of the aedeagus can be used to readily differentiate these two species. In 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Prathapan &amp; Viraktamath" authorityYear="2009" baseAuthorityName="Medvedev" baseAuthorityYear="2001" box="[531,687,963,984]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Tegyrius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="337" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="antennatus" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[531,687,963,984]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="337">T. antennatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="11" pageNumber="337" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, the apex of the aedeagus is smoothly rounded in ventral view (deeply emarginated in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Prathapan &amp; Viraktamath" authorityYear="2009" baseAuthorityName="Medvedev" baseAuthorityYear="2001" box="[576,684,1024,1046]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Tegyrius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="337" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicolor" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[576,684,1024,1046]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="337">T. bicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="11" pageNumber="337" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
), the middle region is slightly narrowed (slightly widened in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Prathapan &amp; Viraktamath" authorityYear="2009" baseAuthorityName="Medvedev" baseAuthorityYear="2001" box="[289,401,1085,1107]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Tegyrius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="337" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicolor" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[289,401,1085,1107]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="337">T. bicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[415,543,1085,1107]" pageId="11" pageNumber="337" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
), and the ventral surface has a pair of ridges enclosing a transparent window (ventral side is transparent and deeply furrowed in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Prathapan &amp; Viraktamath" authorityYear="2009" baseAuthorityName="Medvedev" baseAuthorityYear="2001" box="[267,381,1177,1199]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Tegyrius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="337" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicolor" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[267,381,1177,1199]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="337">T. bicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[397,527,1177,1199]" pageId="11" pageNumber="337" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
). The stem of the tegmen of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Prathapan &amp; Viraktamath" authorityYear="2009" baseAuthorityName="Medvedev" baseAuthorityYear="2001" box="[262,417,1208,1229]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Tegyrius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="337" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="antennatus" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[262,417,1208,1229]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="337">T. antennatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[423,541,1208,1230]" pageId="11" pageNumber="337" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is shorter than the arm (stem is as long as arm in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Prathapan &amp; Viraktamath" authorityYear="2009" baseAuthorityName="Medvedev" baseAuthorityYear="2001" box="[510,616,1238,1260]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Tegyrius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="337" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicolor" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[510,616,1238,1260]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="337">T. bicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[624,747,1238,1260]" pageId="11" pageNumber="337" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
).
</paragraph>
